 The first column provides averages for the entire sample, with corresponding
 standard deviations in parentheses below.
 For instance, we find that the average household in the study cultivated
 maize in about 0.4 acres of land.
 The average age of heads of the household is 42 years and in 44 percent
 of the households, the head finished primary education.
 Households are large, consisting of more than 7 individuals.
 The average household lives about 5.5 km from the nearest input dealer.
 In 30 percent of households, the walls of the house are made of mud and
 the average house has only 2 rooms.
 
